      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">Every Scrabble game starts with exactly 100 tiles in the bag — 98 letters and 2 blanks. Knowing how many of each letter exists is fundamental to strategy. It tells you what your opponents likely hold, what remains in the bag, and whether that word you need is even possible.</p>

